def: Full of rage; expressing rage. [Obs.] "Rageful eyes." Sir P.Sidney.
The European polecat; -- called also European ferret, andfitchew. See Polecat. [Written also foulmart, foulimart, andfulimart.]
One guilty of pederasty; a sodomite.
Pertaining or belonging to the arm; as, the brachial artery;the brachial nerve.
Pertaining to, derived from, or containing, pentyl; as,pentylic alcohol
One who, or that which, diffuses.
Over the rest in authority; above all others; highest. [Obs.]Fabyan.
A subscript mark, number, or letter. See Subscript, a.
To sound; to make a noise. Milton.
